(91, 'facilitate', 'A Shiny application is also developed to facilitate easier implementation and visualization.', 'EnImpute: imputing dropout events in singlecell RNA-sequencing data via ensemble learning', '2023-02-12', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-27'),
(92, 'Extensive', 'Extensive experiments have shown the advantages of EnImpute over the individual imputation methods.', 'EnImpute: imputing dropout events in singlecell RNA-sequencing data via ensemble learning', '2023-02-12', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-27'),
(93, 'rescales', 'After obtaining the imputation results from individual methods, EnImpute rescales the imputed data before combining them.', 'EnImpute: imputing dropout events in singlecell RNA-sequencing data via ensemble learning', '2023-02-12', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-27'),
(94, 'exponentiated', 'First, the imputed expression levels in log-scale (ALRA, DrImpute, MAGIC, scRMD and Seurat) are exponentiated.', 'EnImpute: imputing dropout events in singlecell RNA-sequencing data via ensemble learning', '2023-02-12', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-27'),
(95, 'pseudocount', 'Third, the rescaled imputed data are log transformed with pseudocount 1.', 'EnImpute: imputing dropout events in singlecell RNA-sequencing data via ensemble learning', '2023-02-12', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-27'),
(96, 'robust', 'The trimmed mean is used since it is more robust to outliers than the widely used mean that is computed as the sample average.', 'EnImpute: imputing dropout events in singlecell RNA-sequencing data via ensemble learning', '2023-02-12', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-27'),
(97, 'fraction', 'Users can specify the library size for re-scaling the imputed results and the fraction of observations to be discarded before calculating the trimmed mean by setting the scale.', 'EnImpute: imputing dropout events in singlecell RNA-sequencing data via ensemble learning', '2023-02-12', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-27'),
(98, 'specify', 'Users can specify the library size for re-scaling the imputed results and the fraction of observations to be discarded before calculating the trimmed mean by setting the scale.', 'EnImpute: imputing dropout events in singlecell RNA-sequencing data via ensemble learning', '2023-02-12', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-27'),
(99, 'reveal', 'Clustering and visualization analysis on three scRNA-seq datasets also reveal the advantage of EnImpute over individual methods (Supplementary Section S6).', 'EnImpute: imputing dropout events in singlecell RNA-sequencing data via ensemble learning', '2023-02-12', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-27'),
(100, 'consolidate', 'We first briefly review the eight imputation methods, and then present how to consolidate the results generated by different base methods into a consensus result.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(101, 'consensus', 'We first briefly review the eight imputation methods, and then present how to consolidate the results generated by different base methods into a consensus result.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(102, 'approximation', 'Adaptively-thresholded low rank approximation', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(103, 'affinity', 'Markov affinity-based graph imputation of cells (MAGIC)', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(104, 'deviation', 'The resulting matrix is rescaled so that the mean and standard deviation of each gene in the resulting matrix match that of the original expression matrix.（standard deviation 标准差）', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(105, 'heuristic', 'ALRA develops a heuristic method to choose k based on the statistics of the spacings between consecutive singular values.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(106, 'consecutive', 'ALRA develops a heuristic method to choose k based on the statistics of the spacings between consecutive singular values.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(107, 'singular', 'ALRA develops a heuristic method to choose k based on the statistics of the spacings between consecutive singular values.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(108, 'tuning', 'The key tuning parameter of ALRA is the rank k used in the low rank approximation.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(109, 'heuristic', 'ALRA develops a heuristic method to choose k based on the statistics of the spacings between consecutive singular values.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(110, 'inflated', 'Unlike traditional autoencoders, DCA uses a zero-inflated negative binomial distribution to model the count distribution, overdispersion and sparsity of scRNA-seq data.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(111, 'binomial', 'Unlike traditional autoencoders, DCA uses a zero-inflated negative binomial distribution to model the count distribution, overdispersion and sparsity of scRNA-seq data.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(112, 'overdispersion', 'Unlike traditional autoencoders, DCA uses a zero-inflated negative binomial distribution to model the count distribution, overdispersion and sparsity of scRNA-seq data.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(113, 'sparsity', 'Unlike traditional autoencoders, DCA uses a zero-inflated negative binomial distribution to model the count distribution, overdispersion and sparsity of scRNA-seq data.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(114, 'variations', 'This effectively eliminates the method-tomethod variations in scale.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(115, 'outliers', 'Instead of the standard mean or median which is widely used in ensemble learning, here we use the trimmed mean since it is less sensitive to outliers than the standard mean and uses more information from the observations than the median.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-13', 'paper', 5, '2023-02-28'),
(116, 'pancreatic', 'This is the Human pancreatic islet dataset (GSM2230757). The raw data contains 20,125 genes and 1,937 cells.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-14', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-01'),
(117, 'islet', 'This is the Human pancreatic islet dataset (GSM2230757). The raw data contains 20,125 genes and 1,937 cells.', 'Supplementary Information for the article: \"EnImpute: imputing dropout events in single cell RNA sequencing data via ensemble learning\"', '2023-02-14', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-01'),
(118, 'substitution', 'PAM Matrices are regularly used as substitution matrices to score sequence alignments for protines.', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2Yc2fVNTiH0', '2023-02-15', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-02'),
(119, 'sparse', 'Single-cell data include high-dimensional, sparse, noise and other characteristics, and it is still a challenge to extract the key information of the data through feature extraction to simplify the expression.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-15', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-02'),
(120, 'maturity', 'With the increasing maturity of single cell sequencing technology, the production cost of single cell sequencing data has gradually decreased.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-15', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-02'),
(121, 'specifically', 'Therefore, massive single-cell data are generated in modern scientific research, which is specifically manifested as more single cell number or more gene number.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-15', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-02'),
(122, 'manifested', 'Therefore, massive single-cell data are generated in modern scientific research, which is specifically manifested as more single cell number or more gene number.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-15', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-02'),
(123, 'heterogeneity', 'Compared with previous bulk RNA-seq, scRNA-seq is more beneficial to reveal the heterogeneity of a single cell.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-15', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-02'),
(124, 'mechanism', 'Using the data from the feature selection analysis of single cells can dig deeper into the biology contains important information, assist biologists to explore the potential of disease genes expression mechanism.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-15', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-02'),
(125, 'iteratively', 'The wrapped feature selection method iteratively selects the feature subset from the primitive feature set until the best feature subset is choosed.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(126, 'primitive', 'The wrapped feature selection method iteratively selects the feature subset from the primitive feature set until the best feature subset is choosed.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(127, 'extent', 'When the regularization term increases to a certain extent, all characteristic coefficients tend to zero.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(128, 'coefficient', 'When the regularization term increases to a certain extent, all characteristic coefficients tend to zero.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(129, 'hierarchical', 'The graph representation of single cell data can capture not only the relationships and features among cells, but also the hierarchical relationships among features.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(130, 'multimodal', 'Thus, SIMBA enables multimodal feature discovery and complements current gene regulatory network analysis.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(131, 'copula', 'presented a new method RgCop based on regularized copula, which is a powerful fair dependence measurement and can capture the multivariate dependence among a set of genes in the single cell expression data.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(132, 'multivariate', 'presented a new method RgCop based on regularized copula, which is a powerful fair dependence measurement and can capture the multivariate dependence among a set of genes in the single cell expression data.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(133, 'redundant', 'In order to filter redundant genes, RgCop uses L1 regularization term to punish the redundancy coefficient of genes, so as to carry out gene selection.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(134, 'redundancy', 'In order to filter redundant genes, RgCop uses L1 regularization term to punish the redundancy coefficient of genes, so as to carry out gene selection.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(135, 'significance', 'Kenong Su et al. proposed to calculate feature significance based on initial clustering', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(136, 'burdensome', 'Furthermore, for technical reasons, not only computationally burdensome but also highly expressed genes cannot afford a stabilized and predictive feature set.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(137, 'diagnosis', 'However, in real life, these characteristics of biological value can provide technical support for the regulation of biological system, and provide new ideas for disease diagnosis, drug research and development and other medical fields.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(138, 'robuously', 'it can extract the genetic characteristics of each cell from single-cell sequencing datasets robuously and transfer prior information from annotated datasets to new sequencing datasets quickly and accurately.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-16', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-03'),
(139, 'eigenvalues', 'Then the selected feature set is transformed by calculating the feature vectors with large eigenvalues.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-17', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-04'),
(140, 'taxonomy', 'The introduction of the prior knowledge of tissue-specific cellular taxonomy reference database (CellMatch) can not only find genes that are usually ignored by traditional differential gene expression analysis, but also avoid the influence of subjective factors of researchers to a certain extent.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-17', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-04'),
(141, 'subjective', 'The introduction of the prior knowledge of tissue-specific cellular taxonomy reference database (CellMatch) can not only find genes that are usually ignored by traditional differential gene expression analysis, but also avoid the influence of subjective factors of researchers to a certain extent.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-17', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-04'),
(142, 'extent', 'The introduction of the prior knowledge of tissue-specific cellular taxonomy reference database (CellMatch) can not only find genes that are usually ignored by traditional differential gene expression analysis, but also avoid the influence of subjective factors of researchers to a certain extent.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-17', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-04'),
(143, 'properties', 'Experiments show that its clustering and classification results are more accurate than other methods compared, which means that its feature selection method can capture the potential properties of single-cell data better than other ways.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-17', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-04'),
(144, 'fusion', 'The scFED model is divided into three parts, which are preprocessing, matrix fusion and dimensionality reduction reconstruction.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-17', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-04'),
(145, 'internal', 'In the preprocessing part, the internal entropy mode method is used to remove the noise and select the features with large amount of information to realize the preliminary screening.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-17', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-04'),
(146, 'entropy', 'In the preprocessing part, the internal entropy mode method is used to remove the noise and select the features with large amount of information to realize the preliminary screening.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-17', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-04'),
(147, 'preliminary', 'In the preprocessing part, the internal entropy mode method is used to remove the noise and select the features with large amount of information to realize the preliminary screening.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-17', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-04'),
(148, 'fused', 'Feature engineering is used to get the fused feature while removing noise and reducing dimension.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-17', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-04'),
(149, 'preliminary', 'Then the internal entropy method is used for the preliminary selection of features.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-17', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-04'),
(150, 'consistency', 'The accuracy metrics we use are based on the consistency of cell groupings and cell true labels obtained by clustering methods.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(151, 'grid', 'We conduct a grid search to find the optimal parameters and the optimal solution.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(152, 'grid', 'The transformation matrix is used to reverse the importance of features after dimensionality change and reduction to the original space, and can explain the importance of features in the original space.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(153, 'reverse', 'The transformation matrix is used to reverse the importance of features after dimensionality change and reduction to the original space, and can explain the importance of features in the original space.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(154, 'verification', 'The dimensions reduced by PCA are set as 5, 10, 15, 20, 30, 40 and 50 respectively for verification.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(155, 'decline', 'Based on the experimental results and considering the decline in accuracy and other reasons, the index on the four datasets is integrated, and finally the dimension is set to 10, and then reconstructed.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(156, 'integrated', 'Based on the experimental results and considering the decline in accuracy and other reasons, the index on the four datasets is integrated, and finally the dimension is set to 10, and then reconstructed.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(157, 'intuitive', 'This two-dimensional projection map clearly shows the relationships between cells learned through the model and enables a more intuitive evaluation of the model’s performance.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(158, 'inter', 'However, the scFED model outperforms the IE model in terms of inter-cluster boundedness and intra-cluster clustering in two-dimensional visualization.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(159, 'intra', 'However, the scFED model outperforms the IE model in terms of inter-cluster boundedness and intra-cluster clustering in two-dimensional visualization.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(160, 'identical', 'However, the evaluation indexes of Pollen dataset are not identical with those of scFED model when it is integrated with CellMatch reference database.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(161, 'explosive', 'First, the explosive growth of single-cell data, cell type reference database obviously cannot meet the requirements, more information can be mined to expand such reference database.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(162, 'residual', 'More methods, such as residual production model of semi-supervised learning, will be considered to extend the proposed framework for optimization.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-18', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-05'),
(163, 'filtration', 'In the scFED model, the scRNA-seq dataset is preprocessed using the following steps: normalization and filtration, which is the quality control step, to adjust for differences between individual cell samples.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-20', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-07'),
(164, 'fluctuation', 'In other words, entropy is applied to measure the fluctuation degree of each gene from the gene expression data to provide information genes for accurate clustering/classification analysis in the later stage.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-20', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-07');
INSERT INTO `words` (`index`, `word`, `sentence`, `paper`, `coll_date`, `period`, `next`, `review_date`) VALUES
(165, 'contrast', 'The approaches use for contrast include T-SNE, K-means, PCA, Corr, IE and Seurat.', 'scFED:  Clustering Identifying Cell types of scRNA-seq data based on feature engineering denoising', '2023-02-20', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-07'),
(166, 'catalogues', 'Single-cell RNA sequencing (scRNA-seq) allows researchers to collect large catalogues detailing the transcriptomes of individual cells.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(167, 'detailing', 'Single-cell RNA sequencing (scRNA-seq) allows researchers to collect large catalogues detailing the transcriptomes of individual cells.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(168, 'putative', 'Unsupervised clustering is of central importance for the analysis of these data, as it is used to identify putative cell types.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(169, 'interpretation', 'We also consider the difficulties related to the biological interpretation and annotation of the identified clusters.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(170, 'plethora', 'For centuries, biologists have known that multi­ cellular organisms are characterized by a plethora of distinct cell types.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(171, 'notion', 'Although the notion of a cell type is intuitively clear, a consistent and rigorous definition has remained elusive.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(172, 'intuitively', 'Although the notion of a cell type is intuitively clear, a consistent and rigorous definition has remained elusive.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(173, 'consistent', 'Although the notion of a cell type is intuitively clear, a consistent and rigorous definition has remained elusive.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(174, 'rigorous', 'Although the notion of a cell type is intuitively clear, a consistent and rigorous definition has remained elusive.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(175, 'elusive', 'Although the notion of a cell type is intuitively clear, a consistent and rigorous definition has remained elusive.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(176, 'absence', 'Later, discover­ ies in molecular biology made it possible to character­ ize cell types on the basis of the presence or absence of surface proteins.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(177, 'proteome', 'However, surface proteins represent only a small fraction of the proteome, and it is likely that important differences are not manifested at the cell membrane.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(178, 'membrane', 'However, surface proteins represent only a small fraction of the proteome, and it is likely that important differences are not manifested at the cell membrane.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(179, 'amplification', 'Advances in microfluidics have made it possible to isolate a large number of cells, and along with improve­ ments in RNA isolation and amplification methods, it is now possible to profile the transcriptome of individual cells using next­generation sequencing technologies.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(180, 'numerous', 'The steps upstream of clustering may have a substantial impact on the outcome, and for each step numerous tools are available.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(181, 'consult', 'We encourage the reader to consult recently published overviews of this workflow, as this Review focuses on clustering alone.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(182, 'Broadly', 'Broadly speaking, the goal of clustering is to discover the natural groupings of a set of objects.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(183, 'coher­ent', 'Defining cell types on the basis of the transcriptome is attractive because it provides a data­driven, coher­ent and unbiased approach that can be applied to any sample.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(184, 'spurred', 'This opportunity has spurred the creation of several atlas projects, most notably the Human Cell Atlas.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(185, 'atlas', 'This opportunity has spurred the creation of several atlas projects, most notably the Human Cell Atlas.', 'Challenges in unsupervised clustering of single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-02-22', 'paper', 5, '2023-03-09'),
(186, 'prominent', 'One prominent problem in scRNA-seq data analysis is the prevalence of dropouts, caused by failures in amplification during the reverse-transcription step in the RNA-seq experiment.', 'CIDR: Ultrafast and accurate clustering through imputation for single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-03-08', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-15'),
(187, 'prevalence', 'One prominent problem in scRNA-seq data analysis is the prevalence of dropouts, caused by failures in amplification during the reverse-transcription step in the RNA-seq experiment.', 'CIDR: Ultrafast and accurate clustering through imputation for single-cell RNA-seq data', '2023-03-08', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-15'),
(188, 'doublet', 'In contrast, cells with unexpectedly high counts and a large number of detected genes may represent doublets.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-08', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-15'),
(189, 'disposal', 'We are continuously finding new ways to use the data at our disposal.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-08', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-15'),
(190, 'membrane', 'These outlier barcodes can correspond to dying cells, cells whose membranes are broken, or doublets.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-08', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-15'),
(191, 'mitochondrial', 'For example, barcodes with a low count depth, few detected genes, and a high fraction of mitochondrial counts are indicative of cells whose cytoplasmic mRNA has leaked out through a broken membrane.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-08', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-15'),
(192, 'respiratory', 'For example, cells with a comparatively high fraction of mitochondrial counts may be involved in respiratory processes.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-08', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-15'),
(193, 'exceed', 'For high-count filtering, this proportion should not exceed the expected doublet rate.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(194, 'ambient', 'Ambient gene expression refers to counts that do not originate from a barcoded cell, but from other lysed cells whose mRNA contaminated the cell suspension prior to library construction.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(195, 'lysed', 'Ambient gene expression refers to counts that do not originate from a barcoded cell, but from other lysed cells whose mRNA contaminated the cell suspension prior to library construction.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(196, 'contaminate', 'Ambient gene expression refers to counts that do not originate from a barcoded cell, but from other lysed cells whose mRNA contaminated the cell suspension prior to library construction.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(197, 'suspension', 'Ambient gene expression refers to counts that do not originate from a barcoded cell, but from other lysed cells whose mRNA contaminated the cell suspension prior to library construction.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(198, 'distort', 'These added ambient counts can distort downstream analysis.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(199, 'permissive', 'Often it is beneficial to start with permissive QC thresholds and investigate the effects of these thresholds before going back to perform more stringent QC.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(200, 'investigate', 'Often it is beneficial to start with permissive QC thresholds and investigate the effects of these thresholds before going back to perform more stringent QC.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(201, 'stringent', 'Often it is beneficial to start with permissive QC thresholds and investigate the effects of these thresholds before going back to perform more stringent QC.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(202, 'residual', 'The residuals of the model fit serve as a normalized quantification of gene expression.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(203, 'exhibit', 'Furthermore, plate-based data can exhibit larger variations in count depths per cell than dropletbased data.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(204, 'emphasize', 'In this tutorial, we prefer to separate the normalization and data correction (batch correction, noise correction, etc.) steps to emphasize different processing stages of the data.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(205, 'spurious', 'It should however be noted that log transformation of normalized data can introduce spurious differential expression effects into the data.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-09', 'paper', 4, '2023-03-16'),
(206, 'constitute', 'Gene normalization constitutes scaling gene counts to have zero mean and unit variance.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(207, 'canonical', 'Firstly, distances between log-transformed expression values represent log fold changes, which are the canonical way to measure changes in expression.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(208, 'mitigate', 'Secondly, log transformation mitigates (but does not remove) the mean–variance relationship in single-cell data.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(209, 'crude', 'While scRNA-seq data are not in fact log-normally distributed (Vieth et al, 2017), these three effects make the log transformation a crude, but useful tool.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(210, 'pitfall', 'Pitfalls and recommendations', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(211, 'covariate', 'Data correction targets further technical and biological covariates.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(212, 'interpret', 'These methods can also be used to regress out other known biological effects such as mitochondrial gene expression, which is interpreted as an indication of cell stress.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(213, 'irrespective', 'Irrespective of computational methods, the best method of batch correction is pre-empting the effect and avoiding it altogether by clever experimental design.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(214, 'demultiplex', 'It is possible to demultiplex cells that were pooled in the experiment.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(215, 'denoising', 'A further type of technical data correction is expression recovery (also denoising or imputation).', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(216, 'imputation', 'A further type of technical data correction is expression recovery (also denoising or imputation).', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(217, 'prominent', 'A particularly prominent aspect of this noise is dropout.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(218, 'scenario', 'Given the difficulty of assessing successful expression recovery in a practical application, this scenario represents a challenge to the user pondering whether or not to denoise their data.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(219, 'ponder', 'Given the difficulty of assessing successful expression recovery in a practical application, this scenario represents a challenge to the user pondering whether or not to denoise their data.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-10', 'paper', 3, '2023-03-14'),
(220, 'omit', 'Cell and gene QC should always be performed and is therefore omitted from this characterization.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-13', 'paper', 1, '2023-03-14'),
(221, 'variability', 'In contrast, correcting data for unwanted variability replaces zero expression values.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-13', 'paper', 1, '2023-03-14'),
(222, 'approximation', 'The corrected data layer represents the “cleanest” version of the data, which is the closest approximation of the underlying biological signal.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-13', 'paper', 1, '2023-03-14'),
(223, 'aforementioned', 'The aforementioned characteristics determine the suitability of the pre-processed data for particular downstream applications.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-13', 'paper', 1, '2023-03-14'),
(224, 'delineate', 'To clarify this situation to a new user, we delineated pre-processing into five stages of data processing.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-13', 'paper', 1, '2023-03-14'),
(225, 'retain', 'By scaling count data with a cell-specific factor, global scaling normalization methods retain zero expression values even after log(x+1)-transformation.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-13', 'paper', 1, '2023-03-14'),
(226, 'emphasize', 'This data layer emphasizes dominant aspects of the data, which can be described using a reduced set of features.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-13', 'paper', 1, '2023-03-14'),
(227, 'exploratory', 'Thus, reduced data are used for exploratory methods that require data summaries.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-13', 'paper', 1, '2023-03-14'),
(228, 'inherently', 'Should raw data be presented for visual comparison, the user is required to inherently understand the biases in the data in order to interpret the results.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-13', 'paper', 1, '2023-03-14'),
(229, 'insight', 'After pre-processing, methods that we call downstream analysis are used to extract biological insights and describe the underlying biological system.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-13', 'paper', 1, '2023-03-14'),
(230, 'denote', 'small changes in gene expression between similar cells denoting continuous (differentiation) trajectories', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-13', 'paper', 1, '2023-03-14'),
(231, 'modularity', 'The optimized modularity function includes a resolution parameter, which allows the user to determine the scale of the cluster partition.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-14', 'paper', 0, '2023-03-14'),
(232, 'conceptually', 'Conceptually, the Louvain algorithm detects communities as groups of cells that have more links between them than expected from the number of links the cells have in total.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-14', 'paper', 0, '2023-03-14'),
(233, 'tempting', 'While it may be tempting to assume that the clusters detected in single-cell data represent cell types, there are several axes of variation that determine cellular identity.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-14', 'paper', 0, '2023-03-14'),
(234, 'ongoing', 'Thanks to recent and ongoing efforts such as the mouse brain atlas.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-14', 'paper', 0, '2023-03-14'),
(235, 'constrain', 'It should be noted that the latter method constrains the user to the classical understanding of cell types derived from bulk expression studies, rather than cell identities.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-14', 'paper', 0, '2023-03-14'),
(236, 'permutation', 'To obtain an appropriate measure of significance in clustered data, one can use a permutation test to account for the clustering step.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-14', 'paper', 0, '2023-03-14'),
(237, 'elaborate', 'This test is elaborated on in Appendix Supplementary Text S3.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-14', 'paper', 0, '2023-03-14'),
(238, 'loosely', 'In the first instance, we can loosely verify marker genes via visual inspection.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-14', 'paper', 0, '2023-03-14'),
(239, 'univariate', 'This univariate approach to cluster annotation, although common, is however not recommended outside specific cases.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-14', 'paper', 0, '2023-03-14'),
(240, 'diversity', 'This aspect must be considered especially when computing marker genes for datasets with low cellular diversity.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-14', 'paper', 0, '2023-03-14'),
(241, 'investigation', 'As mentioned above, reference atlases will not contain exactly the same cell identities as the dataset under investigation.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-14', 'paper', 0, '2023-03-14'),
(242, 'coarsely', 'In the interest of speed, automated cell-identity annotation can be used to coarsely label cells and identify where subclustering may be needed.', 'Current best practices in single-cell RNA-seq analysis: a tutorial', '2023-03-14', 'paper', 0, '2023-03-14');
